The paper deals with the application of convolutional codes in random network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the construction and decoding of these codes, which falls under the category of coding theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of these codes for error correction in network coding, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and parallel and distributed computing (cs.CC).
